Hello, please act as a world-class senior frontend engineer. Your task is to build a complete web application based on the following specifications and code files. The final result should be an exact replica of the current project state. The user's original requests were in Romanian.
1. Project Description & Visual Design
The goal is to create a premium/luxury chauffeur service website based on an image provided by the user.
Key Visual Elements:
Theme: A modern, luxurious, dark theme. The primary background color is a very dark grey (#121212), with content blocks having a slightly lighter dark grey background (#1a1a1a).
Accent Color: A gold/tan color (#c0a062) is used for highlights, buttons, and important text.
Typography: Headings use a serif font ('Playfair Display'), while body text uses a sans-serif font ('Roboto').
Header: A sticky header containing the logo "CSS Top ApS" on the left and navigation links ("Servicii", "Rezervări", "Contact") on the right.
Hero Section: A prominent section with the main heading "Excelență in Mișcare", a subheading "Service Premium Chauffer with Premium", a call-to-action button "Rezervă acum", and a high-quality image of a black Mercedes S-Class car. Below this, there are three feature cards for "Punctualitate", "Discreție", and "Confort Premium".
Booking Section: A two-column layout with text on the left and a booking form on the right.
Features/Contact Section: A section with a list of features/details on the left and a map image on the right.
Footer: A simple footer with a closing message and copyright information.
2. Functional Requirements
The website should be a single-page application.
The navigation links in the header must be functional and scroll smoothly to the corresponding sections on the page.
The link mappings are as follows:
"Servicii" should link to the Features Section (FeaturesSection.tsx). This section must have the ID servicii.
"Rezervări" should link to the Booking Section (BookingSection.tsx). This section must have the ID rezervari.
"Contact" should link to the Footer (Footer.tsx). This section must have the ID contact.
3. Project Files & Code
Here is the complete source code for all the files in the project. Please create these files with the exact content provided below.
